data.title: Maddie Ziegler Reveals 30 Random Facts About Herself
data.meta_description:
Leap! star Maddie Ziegler sits down with Teen Vogue and reveals 30 completely random facts about herself including her major crush on Zac Efron, her obsession with Harry Styles, and her all-time favorite smells!
Maddie's new film "LEAP!" is out in theaters August, 25th.
data.text:
I love movies with Zac Efron but I get jealous

of the girls that he gets to date

because I wanna be the girl.

Hi, I'm Maddie Ziegler and today,

I'm here with Teen Vogue and I'm gonna tell you

some random facts about myself that you might not know.

My full name is Madison Nicole Ziegler.

Nickname, when I was little, I was called Maddie Moo Moo.

Now, Tonya, my makeup artist, calls me Maddie girl.

My sign is a Libra.

My birthday is September 30th, 2002.

I know, I'm young okay.

My biggest pet peeve is when the fork

hits the plate and it just scrapes.

Ugh, it's hurting my ears right now.

My weirdest quirk, oh, I do some weird accents.

Hey y'all, my name's Petunia and I love corn

and I live on a ranch with my pigs and cows.

My favorite food would probably be strawberries

or ice cream or sushi and cereal, sorry.

My favorite thing to order at Starbucks

would be a Venti Very Berry Hibiscus.

A strange food pet peeve for me would be,

like when they place their food and it mixes together,

like, don't put your corn and mashed potatoes and mix them.

That's so gross for me, I don't know why.

I never dyed my hair but when I was about six years old,

my aunt is a hairdresser and she put

a temporary highlight in my hair.

My favorite way to wear my hair would

either be, down or in a top knot.

When I was little, I went through like a very sassy phase.

Everyone would call me Mad Dog,

because I would say I always get sassy.

I didn't like when people would make fun of me

or laugh at me, so I would just get really sassy.

I'm out of that now, at least, I hope I am.

The first thing I notice about somebody when I meet them

would be their personality and I always look at their eyes

for some reason, I don't know why.

My dog is the cutest thing. Her name is Malibu

and she's a Maltipoo and she's four pounds

and she's so little and cute and I love her so much.

My favorite song would probably

be anything Harry Styles right now.

I'm kind of obsessed with him and I

think he's very, very good looking.

My favorite flower would probably be a daisy.

I think they're really, really cute.

My favorite smell, this is really weird.

It's the post office, I don't know why.

I love the smell of mail.

I also love the smell of my garage,

I don't know why, it smells so good.

I literally can fall asleep anywhere.

The other day we were on set. I fell asleep on set

in my bedroom and I fell asleep while they were filming.

Like I literally can sleep anywhere,

I can sleep on the floor at the airport.

It takes me about five to seven minutes

to get ready in the morning.

I don't brush my hair because it's so long

and thick that I can barely brush it so,

I just wake up, change my clothes,

brush my teeth and I'm out the door.

My favorite color is purple, like a lavender,

I think it's beautiful.

I have a bunch of favorite actors and actresses

but, I think Kate Hudson is amazing

and she's one of my biggest inspirations.

My favorite TV show is Gossip Girl.

Love you Chuck Bass.

My favorite movie,

oh, that's a hard one.

I really like Get Out, it's a good movie,

very scary, but it's good.

My favorite like three movies to watch,

would be like a drama, a rom-com and a horror movie.

I'm obsessed with Conjuring.

My favorite Disney princess would be,

Ariel, from Little Mermaid, love that movie.

What I want young people to know is,

chase your dreams if you have them

and if you're passionate about something,

then just go for it.

And there you have it, now you know more about me.

Bye guys.
